ruary, 1914, will be delln\nquent and advertised for sale at pub\nlic auction, and unless payment Is\nmade before, will be sold on the 2d\nday of March, 1914, to pay the delln\nquent assessment, together with the\ncost of advertising and expense of\nsale.\nBy order of the Board of Directors\nL. W. PRYOR, Secretary\nJ5toF5,1914\n$40.00 to $55.00\nSuits for\n$36.50\nFOR TEN DAYS ONLY\nBUY YOUR SPRING SUIT NOW AND SAVE MONEY\nW. D. ELLIOTT. Merchant Tailor\nBROUQHER AVENUE, OPPO 81TB MIZPAI; HOTEL.\nTXG\nSEE THE\nCELEBRATED SALOME DANCER\nFRESH FROM THE GAY LIFE OF FRISCO\nWho will perform in some of her latest specialties every\nhour each night at the\nBIG CASINO\nChange of Program and\nMoving Pictures Nightly\nFRESH MEATS\nFISH\nand\nPOULTRY\nWe Handle Only First-Clsst Nevsds Beef\nTONOPAH-GOLDF1ELD MEAT MARKET\nTHE BANK BUFFET\nARTISTICALLY ARRANGED UNEXCELLED SERVICE\nAN ATMOSPHERE Of CONGENIALITY AND GOOD fELLOWSHIP\nWALTER DRYSDALE, Proprietor\nLOTtiROP-DAVIS COMPANY\n...FOR...\nFancy Groceries. Hard Hardware. Tender China\nTHE PIONEER STORE\nLATEST THINGS IN-\nElectrical Cooking Appliances\nAt Reasonable Prices\nTHE NEVADA-CALIFORNIA POWER CO.\nTONOPAH. NEVADA\nK)LI) MEDAL FLOUR A NEVADA PRODUCT\nFOR NEVADA PEOPLE\nBvery sack absolutely guaranteed to the consumer To be had at all\nJ,rer A,k for It and Inttat on getting this. Accept no ohter aa a sub\natltute.\nMcLEAN McSWEKNEY, Distributors.\nTONOPAH HARDWARK CO.\n-StKteuofS Ui Nye C uunly MeKaiitik- I oinpoiiy\nSOLE AGENTS FOR\nMazda Tungsten Lamps\nCaloric Fireless Cookers\nMILBURN WAGONS\nUniversal Stoves and Ranges\nTONOPAH HARDWARE CO.\nSpecisJ train from Tonopsh la\n'lI at I IS p n ami returning at\nmidnight\nFAN! tlOO HOI, NO TRIP\nArrt.lag sag las leg iloldrtelu\nTONOPAH ANO 80LDFIELO\nfUfiRIMO COMPANY\nTHE\nNORTHERN CONCERT HALL\nDANCE EVERY EVENING\nThe I'uMk U Cordiallv Invited\nSt. Patrick Street\nHear of Big Caiinu\nTHE TONOPAH BANKING CORPORATION\n-Organized 1905...\nUNI! El STATES OLPOSITHY FBI PO